lines.value: silikọ́nu a tetravalent metalloid is a chemical element with the symbol si and atomic number 14
lines.name: Yoruba

lines.value: it is less reactive than its chemical analog carbon the nonmetal directly above it in the periodic table but more reactive than germanium the metalloid directly below it in the table
lines.name: Yoruba

lines.value: controversy about silicon's character dates to its discovery silicon was first prepared and characterized in pure form in 1823
lines.name: Yoruba

lines.value: in 1808 it was given the name silicium from flints with an ium word ending to suggest a metal a name which the element retains in several non english languages
lines.name: Yoruba

lines.value: however its final english name first suggested in 1817 reflects the more physically similar elements carbon and boron
lines.name: Yoruba

lines.value: silicon is the eighth most common element in the universe by mass but very rarely occurs as the pure free element in nature
lines.name: Yoruba

lines.value: it is most widely distributed in dusts sands planetoids and planets as various forms of silicon dioxide silica or silicates
lines.name: Yoruba

lines.value: over 90% of the earth's crust is composed of silicate minerals making silicon the second most abundant element in the earth's crust about 28% by mass after oxygen
lines.name: Yoruba

lines.value: most silicon is used commercially without being separated and indeed often with little processing of compounds from nature
lines.name: Yoruba

lines.value: these include direct industrial building use of clays silica sand and stone
lines.name: Yoruba

lines.value: silica is used in ceramic brick
lines.name: Yoruba

lines.value: silicate goes into portland cement for mortar and stucco and when combined with silica sand and gravel to make concrete
lines.name: Yoruba

lines.value: silicates are also in whiteware ceramics such as porcelain and in traditional quartz based soda lime glass
lines.name: Yoruba

lines.value: more modern silicon compounds such as silicon carbide form abrasives and high strength ceramics
lines.name: Yoruba

lines.value: silicon is the basis of the ubiquitous synthetic silicon based polymers called silicones
lines.name: Yoruba

lines.value: elemental silicon also has a large impact on the modern world economy
lines.name: Yoruba

lines.value: although most free silicon is used in the steel refining aluminum casting and fine chemical industries often to make fumed silica the relatively small portion of very highly purified silicon that is used in semiconductor electronics < 10% is perhaps even more critical
lines.name: Yoruba

lines.value: because of wide use of silicon in integrated circuits the basis of most computers a great deal of modern technology depends on it.silicon is an essential element in biology although only tiny traces of it appear to be required by animals however various sea sponges as well as microorganisms like diatoms need silicon in order to have structure
lines.name: Yoruba

lines.value: it is much more important to the metabolism of plants particularly many grasses
lines.name: Yoruba

lines.value: although neon is a very common element in the universe and solar system it is fifth in cosmic abundance after hydrogen helium oxygen and carbon it is very rare on earth

lines.value: it composes about 18.2 ppm of air by volume this is about the same as the molecular or mole fraction and a smaller fraction in the crust
lines.name: Yoruba

lines.value: the reason for neon's relative scarcity on earth and the inner terrestrial planets is that neon forms no compounds to fix it to solids and is highly volatile therefore escaping from the planetesimals under the warmth of the newly ignited sun in the early solar system

lines.value: even the atmosphere of jupiter is somewhat depleted of neon presumably for this reason

lines.value: neon gives a distinct reddishorange glow when used in either low voltage neon glow lamps or in high voltage discharge tubes or neon advertising signs

lines.value: the red emission line from neon is also responsible for the well known red light of helium neon lasers

lines.value: neon is used in a few plasma tube and refrigerant applications but has few other commercial uses
lines.name: Yoruba

lines.value: it is commercially extracted by the fractional distillation of liquid air

lines.value: it is considerably more expensive than helium since air is its only source

lines.name: Yoruba

lines.value: nigba ti ere juju bẹ̀rẹ̀ awọn ohun elo ti awọn oṣere n lo ni banjo ṣẹ̀kẹ̀rẹ̀ samba ati juju asiko
lines.name: Yoruba

lines.value: nigba ti wọn ko lo gita alapooti mọ ni wọ́n bẹ̀rẹ̀ sii lo banjo
lines.name: Yoruba

lines.value: awọn ohun-elo ibilẹ́ ti wọ́n tun mu wọ inu ere juju ni gagan sakara tabi orun iṣa gudugudu agogo agidigbo tabi molo
lines.name: Yoruba

lines.value: awọn ohun-elo igbalode ti a mu wọ́nu ere juju ni gita ọ̀pọ̀ ilu alasopọ̀ ti ẹnikanṣoṣo maa n lu bongo konga ẹ̀rọ gbohungbohun mikisa busita akọ́diọ̀nu ati duuru afẹnufọn nigba kan ri
lines.name: Yoruba

lines.value: igbagbo yoruba nipa ajodun ibile orin ninu odun ibile odun ibile ero yoruba nipa ajodun ibile
lines.name: Yoruba

lines.value: ajọ̀dun ibilẹ̀ jẹ́ mọ́ bibọ oriṣa kan ti awọn olusin rẹ̀ fi n waju mọ́ra tabi lati fi bẹ̀bẹ̀ tabi san ẹ̀jẹ́ lọ́dọ̀ rẹ̀
lines.name: Yoruba

lines.value: gbogbo iwọ̀nyi wa fun ṣiṣe ifẹ́ rẹ̀
lines.name: Yoruba

lines.value: ajọ̀dun ibilẹ̀ tun le wa fun iranti aṣaaju tabi akọni kan boya ti o tẹ ilu kan do tabi ti o jagun kan lati gba awọn eniyan rẹ̀ silẹ̀ lọ́wọ́ ọ̀ta tabi lọ́wọ́ ibi tabi ijanba kan tabi ti o ṣe ohun manigbagbe kan ti wọn fi n ranti rẹ̀ tabi ti wọ́n fi n ṣọpẹ́ fun un ti wọ́n si ti ipa bẹ́ẹ̀ sọ ọ́ di oriṣa ti wọn yoo maa bọ ti wọn yoo si maa ṣe ẹ̀yẹ fun lọ́dọọdun tabi loorekoore
lines.name: Yoruba

lines.value: agbalogbabo lori orin yoruba iwulo orin yoruba orin yoruba
lines.name: Yoruba

lines.value: orin jẹ ọ̀na kan pataki ti ẹni ti o kọrin fi n gbe ere-ọkan rẹ̀ jade lori ohun ti n jẹ ẹ́ lọ́kan yala nipa ọ̀rọ̀ ara rẹ̀ ọ̀rọ̀ ẹlomiran tabi nipa ọ̀rọ̀ kan lawujọ
lines.name: Yoruba

lines.value: ọ̀kọrin le fi orin mu iwuri ati idunu ba ara rẹ̀ tabi ẹlomiiran
lines.name: Yoruba

lines.value: gẹ́gẹ́ bi alore lawujọ ọ̀kọrin tabi oṣere le fi orin gbe ẹ̀dun ọkan ero awujọ sita eyi ti iba maa fun ni ni inira tabi itẹ̀mọ́lẹ̀ tabi ibanujẹ́ abẹ́nu yala lati ọwọ́ ijọba tabi awọn alaṣẹ kan orin le wa fun lilo ara-ẹni tabi ti awujọ lapapọ̀
lines.name: Yoruba

lines.value: orin le mu ni sapa ṣe ohun ti o dabi ẹni ṣoroo ṣe fun ni nigba miiran
lines.name: Yoruba

lines.value: orin apala apala
lines.name: Yoruba

lines.value: ifaaraorin apala jẹ́ ọ̀kan lara awọn orin yoruba ti wọ́n jẹ́ gbajumọ̀ ni agbegbe ẹ̀gba ijẹ̀bu ọ̀yọ̀ ọ̀sun ati igbomina
lines.name: Yoruba

lines.value: orin ayẹyẹ ni orin apala orin igbalode ni pẹ̀lu
lines.name: Yoruba

lines.value: orin apala ko ni nnkan an se pẹ̀lu ẹ̀sin orisa tabi ibọ kan ti a mọ̀ ni ilẹ̀ yoruba
lines.name: Yoruba

lines.value: orin igbafẹ́ ni orin apala
lines.name: Yoruba

lines.value: ifaaraorin igbalode ni orin fuji
lines.name: Yoruba

lines.value: orin to gbalagboko ni pẹ̀lu
lines.name: Yoruba
